  (3454,'post','coding-with-the-right-code',NULL,3424,'Case Study: Coding with the Right Code','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;By Matthew Moreno, VP of Revenue Cycle Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;We at Exemplar Health Resources see a lot of things come up in our clinics as we aim to achieve optimal collections for medical services rendered. &amp;nbsp;At times we notice trends and want to share those with our website visitors. &amp;nbsp;One recent case we finished was with a physician practice using the wrong code for a new procedure introduced to their line of services. &amp;nbsp;Although this practice had been assured by the medical device manufacturer of the correct code to be used for this innovative procedure, the practice went months without reimbursements. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;The practice went a solid 8 months without reimbursement on this new ''high paying'' procedure from Blue Cross and Blue Shield. &amp;nbsp;The doctor was at his wit''s end about what to do, and even flirted with the idea of suing the device manufacturer. &amp;nbsp;Our phone rings and we go in to speak with the provider about what the problem was, and immediately we knew the issue stemmed with their internal billing department. &amp;nbsp;In short they were data entry people placed in charge of the revenue for a $15 million group practice, and wholly out of their depth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Once the practice joined the Exemplar Network, we were able to go to work to shore up this inefficiency. &amp;nbsp;In this case, it was a complete misunderstanding of proper coding which our personnel were able to identify and restore over $750,000. &amp;nbsp;This sort of problem solving from our years of experience along with availability of capital, adroit leadership, healthcare management expertise, information systems and economies of scale are treasured as major benefits of Exemplar Health Resources affiliated practices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;It is not enough to hire someone with the right background or on a good recommendation from a colleague. &amp;nbsp;What we have discovered, is because this is our business and not simply a J-O-B, we dedicate heart and soul into ensuring Exemplar affiliated practices stays on the razor''s edge to improve collections, remits, and higher revenues for all of our physician practices. &amp;nbsp;These principles lead to greater equity and captial gains at lower tax levels for our physician practice owners.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica; font-size: small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources exists to equip and empower healthcare providers to deliver the highest level of care for their patients, by providing superior business analytics, administration, revenue cycle management, and technologies. &amp;nbsp;To learn more about Exemplar Health Resources, or to join the Exemplar Network, visit &lt;a href=&quot;/contacts&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;exemplarhealthresources.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','2011-11-12 11:50:20','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','Medical Coding: A Case Study','Exemplar Health Resources Practices Discover Medical Coding Is Much More than Simple Data Entry Partnering with Practices for Higher Revenues Production, Lower Costs, and Greater Health Outcomes','',NULL,'2011-10-27 15:29:06','n','','Medical Coding is Much More Than You Think',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
  (3450,'post','practice-preparation-for-5010',NULL,3424,'5010 Is Your Practice Ready?','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;On January 1, 2012, the health care industry will be required to conduct the current HIPAA electronic transactions, including claims submission, remittance advice, eligibility, claims status, referral authorizations, and others, using the upgraded 5010 version.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Preparation for the switch and the subsequent cash-flow impact starting in 2012 is essential.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;This resource is an overview to help practices become 5010 compliant before the January 2012 deadline.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;It is important to remember that claims will be rejected and cash-flow will be interrupted if transactions are not transmitted under 5010 Guidelines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 2.4pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources has teamed up with several of our practices to prepare and establish the protocols and processes within practices to have positive effects for the 5010 regulations.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Many of the common needs of all practices have been systematized and formed into methods to assist practices for 5010 compliance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 2.4pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 2.4pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources along with the American Medical Association recommends the following steps to successfully implement the 5010 transactions prior to the January 1, 2012 compliance date.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 2.4pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Contact the vendors you rely on for your successful claims and remittance (i.e. EHR/PM systems, clearinghouses, business associates, billing vendors, coding facilities) to ensure their compliance and upgrades necessary for 5010.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Testing and Training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: left; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; mso-line-break-override: none; word-break: normal; punctuation-wrap: hanging;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/