  (3457,'post','accountable-care-organization-final-rule',NULL,3424,'Accountable Care Organization Final Rule','&lt;div style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: 10px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 8px;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;By Matthew Moreno, VP of Revenue Cycle Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid (CMS) under the Department of Health and Human Serivces, have issued their final rule documentation of which over 600 pages delineates the rules whereby physicians and other healthcare providers can unite for the quality care of Medicare beneficiaries. &amp;nbsp;Exemplar Health Resources has the opportunity to sift through much of the rule''s nuances and caveats to ensure our practices receive the highest level of understanding and strategy as it concerns the practice of medicine in their environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The Final Rule has two main features that HHS is trumpeting as key,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Medicare Shared Savings Program&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Advanced Payment&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;model which provides the rules by which ACOs will operate and the payments tied to quality outcomes respectively. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;The Medicare Shared Savings Program&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;will provide incentives for participating health care providers who agree to work together and become accountable for coordinating care for patients.&amp;nbsp; Providers who band together through this model and who meet certain quality standards based upon, among other measures, patient outcomes and care coordination among the provider team, may share in savings they achieve for the Medicare program.&amp;nbsp; The higher the quality of care providers deliver, the more shared savings the providers may keep.&lt;a style=&quot;mso-footnote-id: ftn1;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; name=&quot;_ftnref1&quot; href=&quot;#_ftn1&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;[1]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;The Advance Payment model&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;will provide additional support to physician-owned and rural providers participating in the Medicare Shared Savings Program who also would benefit from additional start-up resources to build the necessary infrastructure, such as new staff or information technology systems.&amp;nbsp; The advanced payments would be recovered from any future shared savings achieved by the Accountable Care Organization.&lt;a style=&quot;mso-footnote-id: ftn2;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; name=&quot;_ftnref2&quot; href=&quot;#_ftn2&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Verdana;&quot;&gt;[2]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;div style=&quot;mso-element: footnote-list;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Physicians within the Exemplar Health Resources network will receive information and guidelines referring to these rules and further measures as we comb through the data found in the extensive final rule for Accountable Care Organizations. &amp;nbsp;For more information on Exemplar Health Resources or to join Exemplar Health Resources, please visit our website at &lt;a href=&quot;/home&quot;&gt;exemplarhealthresources.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br clear=&quot;all&quot; /&gt;&lt;hr style=&quot;font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; size=&quot;1&quot; width=&quot;33%&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;div id=&quot;ftn1&quot; style=&quot;mso-element: footnote;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoFootnoteText&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;MsoFootnoteReference&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Cambria;&quot;&gt;[1]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;U.S. Department of Health and Human Services&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2011pres/10/20111020a.html&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;http://www.hhs.gov/news/press/2011pres/10/20111020a.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoFootnoteText&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;[2]&amp;nbsp;Ibid.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div id=&quot;ftn2&quot;&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;MsoFootnoteText&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 10px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;a style=&quot;mso-footnote-id: ftn2;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; name=&quot;_ftn2&quot; href=&quot;#_ftnref2&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;','2011-11-14 11:33:08','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','','ACOs are Taking Root as the Delivery Method for CMS, and the Final Rule Issued by CMS will Affect How to Arrange ACOs in Today''s Healthcare Industry','',NULL,'2011-10-31 07:32:19','n','','Accountable Care Organization Final Rule',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
