  (3466,'post','arbitrage-in-healthcare',NULL,3424,'Arbitrage in Healthcare','&lt;p&gt;Through years of development in the world of finance, there are applicable lessons to be gleaned for any market.&amp;nbsp; The changes of the aggregate across all markets is showing an information problem.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;The problem of hidden information leads to market inefficiencies.&amp;nbsp; Market inefficiencies expose us to the opportunity for arbitrage, and although these concepts have been mainly relegated to places like New York, Chicago, and London trading houses, we believe there are market inefficiencies within the healthcare industry which, when exploited, can lead to higher production, lower costs, and greater health outcomes.&amp;nbsp; Which is a wholesale reversal of the current healthcare epidemics of lower productivity, higher costs, and ineffective patient treatment.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Washington believes that to solve this inexorable dilemma, the US government must jettison fee-for-service models and replace them with Accountable Care Organizations (ACOs), Advance Payment models, and Health Maintenace Organization models targeting the last of the triad of inefficiencies above.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources has been studying with adroit financial minds to take on the other two problems thus creating a comprehensive solution.&amp;nbsp; Improving on patient outcomes is only one part of the overall ineffective healthcare industry, and the other two must be addressed or the best minds in America will cease applying to medical school. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;With physician shortages all around the world, the best course of action is to use arbitrage against these inefficiencies to gain an overall advantage.&amp;nbsp; Applying the guides and metrics of arbitrage to medical practices, Exemplar''s Network of practices have been showing improvements in all aspects - higher production, lower costs, and greater patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;This quick guide is an introduction to both arbitrage, and how it can utilized in the healthcare industry to save it.&amp;nbsp; Exemplar Health Resources&amp;nbsp;exists to equip and empower healthcare providers to deliver the highest level of care for their patients, by providing superior business analytics, administration, revenue cycle management, and technologies at the physician&amp;rsquo;s specific direction.&amp;nbsp; We hope this resource Arbitrage in Healthcare will be useful to you and your practice.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4 class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;Download&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Arbitrage in Healthcare (PDF)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;','2011-11-09 12:57:13','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','Arbitrage in Healthcare','Arbitrage in Healthcare as the Solution to Higher Production, Lower Costs, and Greater Patient Outcomes','',NULL,'2011-11-09 12:16:57','n','','Arbitrage in Healthcare',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
  (3463,'post','patient-accounts-common-sense-and-a-little-effort',NULL,3424,'Patient Accounts: Common Sense and a Little Effort','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;By Matthew Moreno, VP of Revenue Cycle Management&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;In a meeting with a practice recently, they were bemoaning the side of the business that everyone is wary about &amp;ndash; patient accounts.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Many times our conversations take off in the direction of &amp;lsquo;Well what can I do about my patient accounts?&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;This is a quandary for healthcare providers.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The healthcare physicians deliver is the most intimate and personal service we receive as consumers, and the care physicians give is often in a vulnerable, intrusive, and confidential environment.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;There are things said and done with your physician that at times are not even mentioned to a spouse, and now physicians are left in that awkward position to say, &amp;lsquo;Now pay me&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;These moments are not easy, so strategies can be created to accommodate this market inefficiency.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Our practices follow 5 simple steps to ensure payment and avoid uncomfortable financial situations with patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;1. Verify.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;By verifying the benefits prior to the patient&amp;rsquo;s appointment, you can be certain that before the encounter, that benefits have been articulated and explained prior to the visit occurring and that intimate care delivered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;2. Co-pay receipts.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;It is a proven fact that it is 62% less likely to receive a payment from a patient once they are out the door.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Make sure that payments are received for every visit, including deductibles, co-insurance, out-of-pocket, and co-pays due to the practice.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;These amounts you will know if you are verifying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;3. Coordination of Benefits.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Follow up with the insurance companies and become students of benefits.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Understand the methods and the nuances of their insurance products to better communicate and coordinate with patients.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;If you have authoritative information regarding the intricacies of the plans, then communicating it to the patient prior to the patient receiving a statement will increase the likelihood of the patient paying, because they are forewarned.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;4. Send Statements.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;This may seem perfectly obvious, but our data shows only 75% of practices send statements on a routine basis (bi-monthly or monthly).&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Proficient billing departments and RCM firms will send patient statements 3 times for 90 days before considering write-offs or delinquency measures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;5. Call the patient.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;After the first four steps are completed, if you have not received the owed balances, do not hesitate to call them.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;We hear that people do not want to have that uncomfortable conversation with a patient they are going to have to see again &amp;ndash; what?!?!&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The uncomfortable time is when they arrive at the clinic, an alert pops up, and Susie at the front-desk has to say, &amp;lsquo;Um, Ms. Jones&amp;hellip;uh, do you&amp;hellip;.uh have payment&amp;hellip;ya know, for the uh&amp;hellip;.outstanding, ya know balance?&amp;rsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Now that is uncomfortable.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Think about it, the patient has been verified with benefits explained, paid subsequent co-pays, etc, has had the billing department or other staff explain and coordinate the benefits, and has received 3 statements.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;This is not a difficult phone conversation to have relative to the very uncomfortable conversation in the practice the day of a sick visit.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Having a plan of action and sticking to the plan can help diminish this inefficiency we see time and again in practices.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources&amp;nbsp;exists to equip and empower healthcare providers to deliver the highest level of care for their patients, by providing superior business analytics, administration, revenue cycle management, and technologies at the physician&amp;rsquo;s specific direction.&lt;span style=&quot;mso-spacerun: yes;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: x-small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;To learn more about Exemplar Health Resources, and to join the Exemplar network, visit &lt;span style=&quot;color: #000000;&quot;&gt;exemplarhealthresources.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','2011-11-03 06:27:00','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','','','',NULL,'2011-11-03 06:15:34','n','','Patient Accounts',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
  (3467,'page','guide-to-setting-practice-goals','',3448,'Guide to Setting Practice Goals','&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/userfiles/media/file/Setting%20Practice%20Goals(4).pdf&quot;&gt;Guide to Setting Practice Goals (PDF)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;We recently put together this self-examination guide to practice goals so as to assist our practices (and perhaps others) to take the first steps to better practice development and management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Our hope is you will be able to utilize this resource from Exemplar Health to continue to grow your practice as you deliver optimal healthcare for patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources exists to equip and empower healthcare providers to deliver the highest level of care for their patients, by providing superior business analytics, revenue cycle management, administration, practice development, and technologies at the physician&amp;rsquo;s specific direction. &amp;nbsp;To join the Exemplar Health Network, please visit us at &lt;a href=&quot;/contacts&quot;&gt;exemplarhealthresources.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small; font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','2011-12-29 08:08:42','y','','','','n','Medical Practice Goals','Establishing Your Physician Practice Goals is Essential to Success, and This Guide Will Be a Good First Step To Develop Your Practice','',NULL,'2011-11-20 16:10:34','n','','PDF for Download to Examine Your Practice',12,12,'y','y','',NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','','examplar',NULL),
  (3474,'post','cost-of-practicing-medicine',NULL,3424,'Cost of Practicing Medicine','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;With the release of the MGMA 2011 Evolving Healthcare Environment Status and Readiness Report, we put together a brief summary of the current layout of costs within private practices. &amp;nbsp;Along with data on the current position most practices have, we make a few recommendations to reduce costs in the age of the Affordable Care Act.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: small;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/userfiles/media/file/Cost%20of%20Medicine(1).pdf&quot;&gt;Cost of Practicing Medicine (PDF)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;','2011-12-30 06:03:53','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','Revenue Cycle Management with Exemplar Health and Physician Medical Billing','Accountable Care Coordination ','Revenue Cycle Management, RCM Services',NULL,'2011-12-29 13:49:57','n','','',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
  (3475,'post','increase-revenue-lower-costs',NULL,3424,'Increase Revenue - Lower Costs','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: xx-large;&quot;&gt;61% &lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;of physicians reported managing their own billing is a ''considerable or extreme challenge''&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;In 2012, reimbursements will be cut dramatically by Medicare, with MGMA predicting up to 29% in lower physician payments. This measure is fueled to accommodate the much maligned sustainable growth rate (SGR). The SGR began in 1997 to slow the expansion of Medicare spending, but with Medicare&amp;rsquo;s greatest expense being claim payments, physician practices are affected the most.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Congress has acted to reduce Medicare payments to providers by abandoning the recent payroll tax cut expiration. What typically follows, commercial payers will reduce payments by pegging their allowed amounts to Medicare. One example is Blue Cross and Blue Shield Association. Many fee schedules from BC/BS and commercial payers are relative to Medicare reimbursements at or around 130% of Medicare allowed amounts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;The option to reject Medicare patients is not viable, as Medicare accounts for more than 20% of physician payments, with baby boomers soon to be Medicare beneficiaries increasing that percentage. This would have devastating effects to private practices who would lose a large patient population, not to mention the loss of patients by leaving commercial networks. Physicians must look inward and find new ways to cut costs and grab every owed dollar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Exemplar Health Resources assists physicians experiencing this burden by providing economies of scale with our revenue cycle management, proprietary software, and professional coding to ensure every claim is paid at the highest possible level. These measures allow practices to outsource their entire back office and billing operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;h3 class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Struggles with In-House Billing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Average Days Outstanding is 54.6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;In 2010, 12% of collectible A/R was written off&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;26% of A/R are patient balances&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Over 45% of patient accounts are never collected&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;FTE for certified biller is over $55,000/year&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Physicians spend 120+ hours on billing related issues annually&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;&quot;&gt;Clinical staff waste over 900 hours on billing related issues annually&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: xx-small;&quot;&gt;Sources: Physicians Practice, February 2010 , MGMA 2011 Evolving Healthcare Environment Status and Readiness Report, and 2009 MBMA Medical Practice Today: What Members Have to Say&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;','2012-01-01 13:29:28','y',NULL,NULL,NULL,'n','Outsourced Medical Billing Physicians Cuts Costs and increase Revenue','Using outsourced billing and revenue cycle management from Exemplar Health Resources can deliver lower costs for physicians and increase revenue with insurance payers.','Revenue Cycle, Outsourced Billing, Medical Billing',NULL,'2012-01-01 13:25:50','n','','Physicians Must Aim to Lower Costs and Increase Revenues in an Age of Payment Reform',12,12,'y','y',NULL,NULL,'n',NULL,'y','n','',NULL,NULL),
